<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11940&amp;p=135305#p135305"><![CDATA[
My guesses as to how they did each effect (by YouTube timing):<br />0:40 probably mode 7 with matrix HDMA, like a racing game with hills<br />1:11 probably window HDMA, the technique used in Super Mario Kart to draw what place you're in. I see artifacts in the elbow associated with the limit of 2 windows per line.<br />1:27 that's a mode 7 floor with some sprites difference-blended onto the bottom<br />1:58 on some other platforms you'd get a metaball effect at this point in the demo, but the Super NES can't do that so instead you get sprites sum-blended over the background<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Oct 21, 2014 5:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
